title: Wausau area athletes of the week
text:
Wausau area athletes of the week Tim Johnson , Daily Herald Media 12:19 a.m. CDT October 22, 2015 Buy Photo 
Sophomore 
Swimming 
The Evergreens second-year varsity swimmer won the 100 yard backstroke and was second to freshman teammate Emma Van Ermen in the 200 IM as the Evergreens downed Wausau East in a Wisconsin Valley Conference dual meet last week. Peterson also won the 100 backstroke Tuesday as the Evergreens finished second to Wausau East in the City Meet. D.C. Everest hosts Wausau West Thursday. 
Emmy Sheehan 
Senior 
Cross country 
The Warriors veteran runner finished third overall in the Wisconsin Valley Conference meet last Saturday, completing the 5,000 meter course at Nine Mile Recreation Area in 20 minutes, 1.1 seconds. Sheehan was one of three West runners to finish in the Top 10 as the Warriors finished second to Stevens Point Area Senior High in the girls team competition. West competes in the WIAA Division 1 sectional meet Saturday at Standing Rocks Park in Stevens Point. Buy Photo 
Senior 
Football 
The Raiders veteran back rushed for 152 and five touchdowns to help Marathon claim an outright Marawood Conference championship with a win over Auburndale. Gassner, who missed his junior season with an injury, finished the regular season with 1,083 yards rushing and 20 touchdowns for the 8-1 Raiders. Marathon hosts Crandon in a WIAA Division 6 Level 1 playoff game Friday. Buy Photo 
Senior 
Football 
Mosinee's kicker hit a 44 yard field goal with 24 seconds to give his team a 30-29 win over Lakeland last wee in the final game of the regular season. The kick completed a comeback for a Mosinee team which scored nine points over the final 4:06 of regulation. With the win, Mosinee improved to 5-3 overall and 4-2 in the GNC. Mosinee, seeded sixth in WIAA Division 3, travels to Antigo on Friday in a Level 1 playoff matchup. Read or Share this story: http://wdhne.ws/1RXEWUw TOP VIDEOS
